# Cross-Agent Rules

Always follow these protocols. Full details: [.cursor/workflow/](../workflow/) and [docs/STANDARD.md](../../docs/STANDARD.md).

## CALEW Orchestration (v1)

CALEW commands are conventions ‚Äî treat `/hey-manager` the same as `@10-manager`. Router skill: [calew-router](../skills/calew-router/SKILL.md). Human reference: [SKILLS.md](../../SKILLS.md).

| CALEW command | Cursor rule |
|---------------|-------------|
| `/hey-manager` | `@10-manager` |
| `/hey-architect` | `@20-architect` |
| `/hey-developer` | `@30-developer` |
| `/hey-qa` | `@40-qa` |
| `/hey-tester` | `@40-qa` (execute_only mode) |
| `/hey-devops` | `@50-devops` |

**Three interaction types:**
- **Invoke** ‚Äî `/hey-{agent}` ‚Äî adopt persona, take ownership
- **Consult** ‚Äî `/talk-to` ‚Äî ask opinion; owner keeps `active_agent` ([consultation-protocol.md](../workflow/consultation-protocol.md))
- **Transfer** ‚Äî `/handoff-to` ‚Äî pass ownership after gate pass ([calew-handoff](../skills/calew-handoff/SKILL.md))

**Session:** Update [.cursor/session/state.yaml](../session/state.yaml) on invoke and handoff. Status: `/calew-status`.

**Safety:** No auto-handoff. No production deploy without human approval. When unsure: `/hey-manager`.

## Communication

Use artifact-first messages per [communication-protocol.md](../workflow/communication-protocol.md):
- Include date, tier, phase, related doc paths
- Record decisions in versioned docs, not chat-only

## Handoffs

Before transferring work between agents, complete the checklist in [handoff-procedures.md](../workflow/handoff-procedures.md) and verify [quality-gates.yaml](../workflow/quality-gates.yaml).

| Transition | Gate key |
|------------|----------|
| Manager ‚Üí Architect | `manager_to_architect` |
| Architect ‚Üí Manager (escalation) | `architect_to_manager` |
| Architect ‚Üí Developer | `architect_to_developer` |
| Developer ‚Üí QA | `developer_to_qa` |
| QA ‚Üí Developer (failure) | `qa_to_developer` |
| QA ‚Üí DevOps | `qa_to_devops` |
| DevOps ‚Üí Manager | `devops_to_manager` |

## Escalation

Classify issues P0‚ÄìP3 per [escalation-matrix.md](../workflow/escalation-matrix.md). P0/P1 block release until resolved or explicitly accepted by Manager.

## Documentation

All new docs require YAML frontmatter (title, version, created, updated, owner, reviewers, status, tags, audience, tier). No `TODO`, `TBD`, or `fill in later` in `approved` docs.

## Tier Model

Detect tier via [scaling-indicators.yaml](../workflow/scaling-indicators.yaml). Skip docs listed under `simplify.skip_docs` for T1 only when tier exception is logged in sprint notes.

## Quality Gates (summary)

- Lint errors: 0 before QA handoff
- Unit coverage: T1 60%, T2 80%, T3 85%
- Open P0/P1 defects: 0 before deploy
- Gate artifacts: `status: approved`

## Knowledge Transfer

Schedule KT per [knowledge-transfer.md](../workflow/knowledge-transfer.md) on architect‚Üídeveloper handoff and major releases.

